body_html:
The list of supported ops are available here. The two recommended solutions are:

  1. Add a custom op as described here.
  2. Only use the ops that are currently supported by TFLite in your model.

Quantized SquaredDifference hasn't been prioritized yet, contributions are welcome, but we are also tracking these operations requests here: #21526 to help with prioritizing. I have added your request there.

Additionally, as @jdduke mentioned, Merge and Switch are not prioritized and are not in our immediate roadmap due to complexity. For that reason, we will close this issue, please reopen if you have more info on the specific model you are trying to convert. Thanks!

body:
The list of supported ops are available [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/tf_ops_compatibility.md). The two recommended solutions are:
1. Add a custom op as described [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/custom_operators.md).
2. Only use the ops that are currently supported by TFLite in your model.

Quantized `SquaredDifference` hasn't been prioritized yet, contributions are welcome, but we are also tracking these operations requests here: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/21526 to help with prioritizing. I have added your request there.

Additionally, as @jdduke  mentioned, `Merge` and `Switch` are not prioritized and are not in our immediate roadmap due to complexity. For that reason, we will close this issue, please reopen if you have more info on the specific model you are trying to convert. Thanks!
